ABP Marine Environmental Research Ltd. (ABPmer), working jointly with Coastal Engineering UK Ltd (CEUK), has been commissioned by Barrow Borough Council (BBC) to undertake the Roa Island Shorelink Management Plan (SMP) for Sediment Sub-cell 11c: Fleetwood to Walney Isalnd.

The study is being project managed on behalf of Barrow Borough Council (BBC) by Capita, with specialist technical advice provided to Capita by Shoreline Management Partnership.

Specific objectives of the study include:
*To undertake a 'walk-over' survey of the study area, recorded by geo-referenced fixed-aspect digital photographs and an accompanying text report to cover the structural form of the existing defences and relevant environmental issues;
*To determine the water level and wave climate incident on the area, both present-day and over the next 50 years, taking account of climate change.
*To collect and collate available historic data on the study area;
*To determine the tangible asset value of island developments;
*To relate the above objectives to the Shoreline Management Plan by confirming or modifying the plan policies, with recommendations for further work as appropriate;
*To estimate the level of service and residual service life of the existing defences and to identify the typical form, coast and timescale of maintenance and refurbishment.

Each of the above objectives is discussed in turn in the appropriate sections of this report, which follow on from an initial description of the physical, historical, geomorphological and environmental setting of the study area.

